title: High-energy-proton fission cross sections of U,Bi,Au and Ag measured with mica track detectors

x4freetext: High-energy-proton fission cross sections of U,Bi,Au
and Ag measured with mica track detectors

x4freetext: Brookhaven Ags - 13,29 GeV.
Two rectangular pieces of muscovite mica, 1*0.5
inch, 0.1 mm thick, with a fissile layer in between.
For relative beam monitoring.
A calibrated end-window proportional counter,
for absolute beam monitoring, see `Monitor`.
Layers of natural silver, gold, bismuth, and natural
uranium fluoride were evaporated onto the mica in
vacuum. the thickness deposited was about 100 um/cm2
for silver and gold, about 40 um/cm2 for bismuth
and about 10 um/cm2 for uranium.
The mica detectors were photographed
separately. The paired sheets of film were examined on
a light box, where correlated pairs of tracks were
found to be in alignment. These events were identified
as binary fission if each track was >= 1.6 um in
projected length. ternary fission events were
discarded if it appeared likely that they consisted of
a correlated pair of tracks and an accidental unpaired
track.
